@NODE USER_REGISTRATION
  USER REGISTRATION

    HypAss started as a little idea and went a huge project, as you can see
    in the @{" statistics " link hass:doc/-statistics.guide/main}, and I think it's worth to be continued. It may be
    also of your interest that this project will not disappear in a shelter.


  HOW TO GET A REGISTERED USER:

    HypAss is Shareware, as you could read in the copyright notice. So if
    you are interested to get a full user license for HypAss send me 30.-
    german marks (or US $25) by international money order or by cheque.
    This money must *reach* me, I will not pay for an exchange! Then
    print out the 'registration.form' in the docs archive. Fill it out with
    all necessary data, put it in a FREE letter, addressed at yourself,
    containing a formatted 3.5 inch floppy disk (DD or HD) and send it to
    me, and you will receive the latest, registered version of HypAss.
    I will not pay for postage! The postage to you will be at your own risk,
    so think well for which postage system your letter will already be paid
    for when it reaches me.

    Think well about registration *BEFORE* you send me anything! I can't
    give back any money later! You have a good chance to find out now
    weather you like HypAss or not!

    For registered users, any future updates will be FOR FREE!
    (Not the postage) I hate multiple paying for one single piece of
    software, what I've seen very often now.

    Each MAIN AUTHOR (and not the owner of the copyrights) who has ever
    written a freeware assembler for Amiga will get a registration for free!
    Just send me a disk as described before, and "identify" yourself by
    putting your latest assembler version on disk. ;-)


  REGISTRATION DISCLAIMER:

    Although a registration will give you the full license to use HypAss
    according to the conditions stated in this doc, you will not have a
    right for support in future (but a very good chance!). I'm interested
    myself to let HypAss grow, but nobody knows what will be tomorrow.
    Whenever there exist updates, you will have a right to receive them,
    if you send me a disk as described before. Evaluation updates will be
    released by the same electronic channels which brought you this release.
    The earliest place where these updates will occur is of course the
    directory 'aminet/dev/cross', what should signalize to you, that the
    time has come to contact me for a new registered version. This system
    is in the moment prelimary. *Maybe* a keyfile will be sent to registered
    users one day, activating the evaluation versions. Any section of this
    doc except the 'distribution' area still stay valid for registered
    users!


  HOW TO HANDLE A REGISTERED HYPASS:

    In opposite to the evaluation version, the registered version of HypAss
    is *NOT* freely distributable. You are not allowed to give a copy to
    anyone. You are allowed to make a safety backup for yourself. If
    everything breaks down, you may order a new disk from me (as described),
    that's no problem. The registered version of HypAss will carry your
    personal signature, so I can identify any illegal copy running around!
    You will be held responsible for any software piracy which may be a
    result of your registered version, direct or indirect.
    You are *not* allowed to sell your registered version of HypAss!


    SEE ALSO:  @{" Registration.form " link doc/Registration.form/main}


